Nigeria’s leading food manufacturing and marketing company, Nestlé Nigeria, has donated food and beverages worth N32 million to support the Covid-19 palliative efforts of the Rivers State government. The donation was part of the company’s contribution of over N700 million comprising product and cash donations, towards the national response efforts led by the Presidential Task Force on Covid-19. The food and beverages donated by Nestlé would support individuals and families most impacted by the containment measures put in place by the state task force on Covid-19 to stop the spread of the virus. Receiving the donation yesterday in Port Harcourt, secretary to Rivers State Government, Dr. Tammy Danagogo, commended Nestlé Nigeria for being the first to support the government’s efforts towards cushioning the impact of the pandemic on the indigenes and residents of Rivers State.  